the ignore list is handled in Torque3D/Engine/source/T3D/turret/aiTurretShape.cpp
the only current functions exposed to TorqueScript are:

```
%AITurretObj.addToIgnoreList(%shapeBaseObj);
%AITurretObj.RemoveFromIgnoreList(%shapeBaseObj);
```

these torquescript functions would add greater control over the turret's ignore list
and would be very useful.

```
torque script function: 

%AITurretObj.ignoreListCount();

return the number of objects in the turrets ignore list.

returns: zero based count of items in the AITurret's ignore list.

example use in torqueScript: 
%ObjectsIgnored = %AITurretObj.ignoreListCount();
```

```
torque script function: %AITurretObj.getIgnoreListObject( int i );
returns: the ignored object ID at index i of the AITurret's ignore list

example use in torqueScript: 
%IgnoredOBJ = %AITurretObj.getIgnoreListObject(2);

example returns the %obj objectID of the item 2 in the ignore list.
```

example use of how both functions can be useful together in TorqueScript:

```
           for(%count = 0; %count < %AITurretObj.ignoreListCount(); %count++) 
           {
               %AITurretObj.getIgnoreListObject(%count).health += 10;
           }
```

Currently there is no way to clear an object from the ignore list unless you know what the object ID is.
this function can come in useful.

